OL,4,G2200FMarilyn and the Mob
OL,5,     GMarilyn Monroe was 1950s
OL,6,     GHollywood's brightest star. But
OL,7,     Gbeneath Tinseltown's glitz was an
OL,8,     Gindustry shaped by the mob. Did
OL,9,     GMarilyn pay dearly in a brutal
OL,10,     Ggame of power and betrayal?
OL,11,G2300FMarilyn and the Mob
OL,12,     GIn 1962 Marilyn Monroe travels to
OL,13,     GNevada with Frank Sinatra,
OL,14,     Gplacing her amid mobsters and
OL,15,     Gdangerous rumours. Days later,
OL,16,     Gshe's found dead. Was her death
OL,17,     Gjust an accident?
